condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Financing Agreement Article VClause 5.01 | Description :Conditions of effectiveness.(a) The SubsidiaryAgreement has been executed on behalf of the Recipient and the ProjectImplementingEntity. (b) The Loan Agreement has beenexecuted and delivered and conditions precedent to its effectiveness (other than the effectiveness of this Agreement) have beenfulfilled. | Due Date :27-Apr-2012

Finance Agreement :LA Sch 2 I.A.2 | Description :The Borrower shall maintain a project steering committee (PSC) Chaired bySecretary of Ministry of Water and Power with membership and terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :LA Sch 2 I.D and II.AWAPDA PA I.A.3, I.C and II.ANTDC PA I.C, I.D and II.A | Description :WAPDA and NTDCwould: (i) monitor the physical and financial progress of the Project, implementation of the Social Action Plan and Env. Manag.Plan, and the Project impact studies; ii analyze the data on key performance indicators on a regular basis; iii prepare and submitquarterly progress reports; and iv submit annual progress reports each year, and annual work plans for the following year |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement Schedule 2Section I B | Description :GoP shall on-lend the proceeds of the IBRD Loan to WAPDAunder a subsidiary agreement to be entered into between the GoP and WAPDA,under terms and conditions approved by the Bank, whichshould include that (i) WAPDA would be authorized to withdraw proceeds of the loan and credit; and (ii) the proceeds of the Loanand Credit shall be re-lent to WAPDA at the maximum interest rate of 15 percent. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :NTDC PA I.A.1(b) | Description :NTDC would, till completion of the project, appoint Project Director ofTransmission line and staff of PMU for the construction of the transmission line in consultation with and according to the terms ofacceptable to the World Bank and maintain PMU till completion of the Project. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement (PA) Section I, A1 & A14 | Description :Water and Power Development Authority (WAPDA) would,till completion of the Project, with terms of reference (TORs), composition and staffing acceptable to the Bank, maintain theProject Management Unit (PMU) and independent panel of experts (IPOE). | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section I, A12 &A13 | Description :WAPDA would maintain the construction supervisionconsultants (CSCs) and monitoring and evaluation consultant (M&ECs), under TORs and contractual arrangements satisfactory to theBank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section I, A5 | Description :WAPDA would maintain a Resettlement Claims Commission, with TORsand composition satisfactory to the Bank to deal with unresolved resettlement court cases for the Tarbela Dam and Ghazi BarothaHydro Projects. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section I, D3 | Description :WAPDA would establish on-site and maintain a Grievance RedressCommittee (GRC) throughout the Project implementation period with TORs and composition satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section II, A1(a)and A1(b) | Description :WAPDA would: (i) monitor the physical and financialprogress of the Project, implementation of the Social Action Plan & Environmental Management Plan, and the Project impact studies;(ii) analyze data on key performance indicators on a regular basis; (iii) prepare and submit quarterly progress reports; and (iv)submit annual progress reports each year, and annual work plans for the following year | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section II, D | Description :The mid-term review of the Project would be undertaken by October31, 2016. | Due Date :31-Oct-2016

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section II, E2 | Description :Prepare and implement a plan aimed at strengthening the internalaudit function for purposes of compliance with international standards. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section II, E4 | Description :WAPDA would ensure that independent auditors carry out theProject audits in accordance with scope and TORs acceptable to the Bank,which shall include special examination of the controls andcompliance with the agreed upon procurement procedures. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Section III, 2 | Description :WAPDA would establish procurement documentation and recordkeeping systems, including a website showing the status of procurement of various contracts and their performance, and make bothfully operational, and put in place a procurement complaint handling systemby no later than December 31, 2012. | Due Date:31-Dec-2012
